.TH "rpr0521_set_power_state" 9 "rpr0521_set_power_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rpr0521_set_power_state \- handles runtime PM state and sensors enabled status
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rpr0521_set_power_state
.BI "(struct rpr0521_data *data "  ","
.BI "bool on "  ","
.BI "u8 device_mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "data" 12
rpr0521 device private data
.IP "on" 12
state to be set for devices in \fIdevice_mask\fP
.IP "device_mask" 12
bitmask specifying for which device we need to update \fIon\fP state
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calls for this function must be balanced so that each ON should have matching
OFF. Otherwise pm usage_count gets out of sync.
